    <text id="F8029T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Gehr asks Cameron to help secure a clerkship for Gehr's son.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    D. O. Gehr's<lb/><hi rend="underline">Son</hi><lb/>Promised to<lb/>help him
                    to<lb/>a <hi rend="underline">Clerkship</hi><lb/><abbr expan="November"
                        >Nov.</abbr> 1860
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1860-11-10"><abbr expan="November">Nov</abbr> 10/<abbr
                                expan="1860">60</abbr></date>
                        <name type="place">Chambersburg</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Honorable">Hon</abbr> Simon Cameron.</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I introduce to your acquaintance My Son Hastings Gehr, he is desirous of getting
                    a Clerkship this winter at Harrisburg during the Session of the Legislature as
                    transcribing clerk or some post under Forney at Washington City during the
                    Session of Congress, I put him in a law office a few years since and he was
                    admitted to the bar last April, but is not inclined to commence the profession
                    for a few years, would prefer some other calling for the present, any
                    appointance you may render him will be gratefully remembered</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Your Friend</salute>
                    <signed>D. O. Gehr</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
